---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout title="NexGen Binary | Managed IT for Dental & Healthcare Offices" active="home" includeFaqSchema={true}>
  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container hero-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">Virginia-Based IT Support</span>
          <h1>Managed IT for Dental & Healthcare Offices</h1>
          <p class="lead">Responsive, security-focused support for Microsoft 365, devices, networking, and daily office operations—with fully managed and co-managed options.</p>
          <div class="inline-row">
            <a href="/consultation#book" class="btn primary track" data-event="cta_click" data-label="hero_book"><i class="fa-solid fa-calendar-check"></i> Book a Consult</a>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn ghost track" data-event="cta_click" data-label="hero_message"><i class="fa-solid fa-paper-plane"></i> Send Message</a>
          </div>
          <div class="pill-row big">
            <span><i class="fa-brands fa-microsoft"></i> Microsoft 365 Support</span>
            <span><i class="fa-solid fa-shield-halved"></i> Security-First IT</span>
            <span><i class="fa-solid fa-location-dot"></i> Richmond Area Coverage</span>
            <span><i class="fa-solid fa-tooth"></i> Dental & Healthcare Focus</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <aside class="panel">
          <h3>Quick Start</h3>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li>Book a consultation</li>
            <li>Share your office size and IT priorities</li>
            <li>Review Fully Managed or Co-Managed options</li>
            <li>Plan the best next step</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="/services" class="btn primary full track" data-event="cta_click" data-label="hero_explore_services"><i class="fa-solid fa-layer-group"></i> Explore Services</a>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="container">
      <div class="section-head"><h2>Why Practices Choose NexGen Binary</h2></div>
      <div class="grid3">
        <article class="card"><div class="icon-box"><i class="fa-solid fa-network-wired icon"></i></div><h3>Fully Managed IT</h3><p>Proactive monitoring, patching, helpdesk support, and ongoing maintenance for office stability.</p></article>
        <article class="card"><div class="icon-box"><i class="fa-solid fa-map-location-dot icon"></i></div><h3>Local & Responsive</h3><p>Richmond-area support with remote-first triage and onsite coverage when needed.</p></article>
        <article class="card"><div class="icon-box"><i class="fa-solid fa-shield-halved icon"></i></div><h3>Security-Focused Support</h3><p>Practical safeguards, backup checks, MFA support, and documentation-driven service.</p></article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="container">
      <div class="section-head"><h2>Service Plans</h2><p class="muted">Two large plan bubbles with names, info buttons, and full plan details.</p></div>
      <div class="grid2">
        <article class="panel plan-card">
          <div class="plan-head">
            <div class="plan-title">
              <div class="icon-box"><i class="fa-solid fa-network-wired icon"></i></div>
              <div><h3>Fully Managed IT</h3><p class="small muted">Complete outsourced support</p></div>
            </div>
            <button class="toggle-btn" type="button" aria-expanded="true"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i> More Info</button>
          </div>
          <div class="toggle-content open">
            <p>Best for offices that want a single IT partner handling day-to-day support and stability.</p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
              <li>Monitoring and alerting</li><li>Remote helpdesk + onsite support</li><li>Patch management</li><li>Microsoft 365 administration</li>
              <li>Endpoint security support</li><li>Backup monitoring checks</li><li>Network / Wi-Fi support</li><li>Monthly support reviews</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/consultation#book" class="btn primary track" data-event="cta_click" data-label="plan_fully"><i class="fa-solid fa-calendar-check"></i> Book a Consult</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="panel plan-card">
          <div class="plan-head">
            <div class="plan-title">
              <div class="icon-box"><i class="fa-solid fa-people-group icon"></i></div>
              <div><h3>Co-Managed IT</h3><p class="small muted">Partner with internal IT</p></div>
            </div>
            <button class="toggle-btn" type="button" aria-expanded="true"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i> More Info</button>
          </div>
          <div class="toggle-content open">
            <p>Ideal for organizations with internal IT staff who need backup, escalation help, and project support.</p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
              <li>Escalation support</li><li>Project support</li><li>Cloud and M365 assistance</li><li>Vendor coordination</li>
              <li>Security reviews</li><li>Documentation standards</li><li>Overflow coverage</li><li>Flexible collaboration model</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/consultation#book" class="btn primary track" data-event="cta_click" data-label="plan_comanaged"><i class="fa-solid fa-calendar-check"></i> Book a Consult</a>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="container">
      <div class="section-head"><h2>Who We Serve</h2></div>
      <div class="grid3">
        <div class="chip"><i class="fa-solid fa-tooth"></i> Dental Practices</div>
        <div class="chip"><i class="fa-solid fa-stethoscope"></i> Medical Clinics</div>
        <div class="chip"><i class="fa-solid fa-notes-medical"></i> Specialty Practices</div>
        <div class="chip"><i class="fa-solid fa-building-circle-check"></i> Multi-Location Offices</div>
        <div class="chip"><i class="fa-solid fa-user-gear"></i> Internal IT Teams</div>
        <div class="chip"><i class="fa-solid fa-cloud"></i> Microsoft 365 Environments</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="container">
      <div class="section-head"><h2>Service Areas</h2></div>
      <div class="grid3">
        <a class="card link-card" href="/service-area-richmond"><div class="icon-box"><i class="fa-solid fa-city icon"></i></div><h3>Richmond</h3></a>
        <a class="card link-card" href="/service-area-henrico"><div class="icon-box"><i class="fa-solid fa-map icon"></i></div><h3>Henrico</h3></a>
        <a class="card link-card" href="/service-area-chesterfield"><div class="icon-box"><i class="fa-solid fa-location-dot icon"></i></div><h3>Chesterfield</h3></a>
      </div>
      <div class="inline-row top-gap"><a href="https://www.google.com/maps?cid=REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_GBP_ID" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn ghost track" data-event="gbp_click" data-label="home_gbp"><i class="fa-brands fa-google"></i> View Google Business Profile</a></div>
    </section>

    <section class="container">
      <div class="section-head"><h2>Client Feedback</h2></div>
      <div class="grid3">
        <div class="card"><p>“Add your first testimonial here.”</p><small>— Dental Practice (Placeholder)</small></div>
        <div class="card"><p>“Add a short quote about responsiveness and support quality.”</p><small>— Office Manager (Placeholder)</small></div>
        <div class="card"><p>“Add a quote about M365 or project support.”</p><small>— Healthcare Admin (Placeholder)</small></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="container">
      <div class="section-head"><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2></div>
      <div class="faq">
        <details><summary>Do you support dental and healthcare offices?</summary><p>Yes. That is the primary focus of the service model shown on this site.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Do you offer onsite support in the Richmond region?</summary><p>Yes. Remote support is used for speed, and onsite support is available when needed.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Can you work with our internal IT person?</summary><p>Yes. The Co-Managed IT plan is designed for that setup.</p></details>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
